<node id="IABP">
  <data key="d0">IABP</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">IABP stands for intra-aortic balloon pump, a medical device used for hemodynamic support in patients with cardiogenic shock.&lt;SEP&gt;IABP stands for intra-aortic balloon pump, a mechanical device used to support heart function.&lt;SEP&gt;IABP (Intra-aortic Balloon Pump) is a mechanical device used for hemodynamic support, compared against Impella in the clinical trial.&lt;SEP&gt;IABP (intra-aortic balloon pump) is a cardiac assist device used as a comparator to Impella in the clinical trial.&lt;SEP&gt;IABP is an intra-aortic balloon pump used for hemodynamic support in cardiogenic shock patients.&lt;SEP&gt;IABP (Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump) is a medical device used for cardiac support, compared against Impella in a survival probability study.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-991db3b8f843321a27cc49183034d5f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cd12a4d42988a0cbef608f813b7db575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff0702c16a40074abed0254fa2987a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60</data>
