<node id="LVAD">
  <data key="d0">LVAD</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">LVAD stands for left ventricular assist device, a mechanical pump supporting the left ventricle.&lt;SEP&gt;LVAD (Left Ventricular Assist Device) is a mechanical device used to support heart function, mentioned in the context of additional work for patients.&lt;SEP&gt;LVAD is a left ventricular assist device used for hemodynamic support in cardiogenic shock patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-991db3b8f843321a27cc49183034d5f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cd12a4d42988a0cbef608f813b7db575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2</data>
