<node id="Impella LP2.5">
  <data key="d0">Impella LP2.5</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Impella LP2.5 is a catheter-based, impeller-driven, axial-flow pump manufactured by Abiomed Europe GmbH, capable of providing up to 2.5 l/min of flow from the left ventricle to the ascending aorta and is implantable via a percutaneous approach.&lt;SEP&gt;Impella LP2.5 is a type of ventricular assist device used in a clinical trial for cardiogenic shock.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-991db3b8f843321a27cc49183034d5f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2</data>
