</node>
<node id="Investor Concerns">
  <data key="d0">Investor Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Investor concerns refer to the worries of investors regarding rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty, which contributed to the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty are a key factor driving the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty are a key factor driving the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty are driving the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty are a key factor driving the market selloff.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0702c16a40074abed0254fa2987a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a4a995063bc2bf1c53d9019501ce065&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a40dc31e02c5c0febdae8449f769db0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8a835d63382015bc0073fd6f79ae0ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-344323b918fd0a2f63161ea908593c80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc8300849246981a965ff70c583daf4d</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;shchelochkov2019.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780046011</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rising Interest Rates">
  <data key="d0">Rising Interest Rates</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rising interest rates are a macroeconomic factor that has become a key concern for investors, contributing to widespread investor anxiety and market volatility. This phenomenon is identified as a primary driver behind the stock market downturn and the broader market selloff, as it directly influences investor sentiment and financial market stability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0702c16a40074abed0254fa2987a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21216935d007e96698b174a5337c6463&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a4a995063bc2bf1c53d9019501ce065&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a40dc31e02c5c0febdae8449f769db0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8a835d63382015bc0073fd6f79ae0ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-344323b918fd0a2f63161ea908593c80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc8300849246981a965ff70c583daf4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10880be99377e9a685fe866bbe47008f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e776f44c2a2b63585778263cf8b4315</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;shchelochkov2019.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780046014</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulatory Uncertainty">
  <data key="d0">Regulatory Uncertainty</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulatory uncertainty refers to the lack of clarity or the presence of unclear and changing government policies and regulations that affect business operations. This ambiguity is a key factor driving investor concerns, as it makes it difficult to predict future compliance costs, operational constraints, and the overall business environment. Consequently, regulatory uncertainty is a significant contributor to market volatility, often leading to market downturns, selloffs, and declines in specific sectors such as technology stocks. The absence of stable and predictable rules creates an environment of risk that prompts cautious investor behavior and negatively impacts market stability.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulatory uncertainty refers to unclear or changing regulations that negatively impact investor sentiment and market performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulatory uncertainty is a factor contributing to investor concerns and the decline in tech stocks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0702c16a40074abed0254fa2987a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21216935d007e96698b174a5337c6463&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a4a995063bc2bf1c53d9019501ce065&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a40dc31e02c5c0febdae8449f769db0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8a835d63382015bc0073fd6f79ae0ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-344323b918fd0a2f63161ea908593c80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc8300849246981a965ff70c583daf4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10880be99377e9a685fe866bbe47008f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e776f44c2a2b63585778263cf8b4315</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;shchelochkov2019.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780046011</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Reserve">
  <data key="d0">Federal Reserve</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Federal Reserve is the central banking system and central bank of the United States. Its policy decisions are closely watched by financial experts and are expected to influence both investor confidence and overall market stability. The institution’s upcoming policy announcement is a key event anticipated to have a significant impact on these areas.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0702c16a40074abed0254fa2987a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21216935d007e96698b174a5337c6463&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0f3aa4a7c7719cac1f9550ae1f1ae67c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a40dc31e02c5c0febdae8449f769db0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8a835d63382015bc0073fd6f79ae0ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10880be99377e9a685fe866bbe47008f</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;shchelochkov2019.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780046013</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Financial Experts">
  <data key="d0">Financial Experts</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Financial experts are analysts and professionals who monitor market conditions and the actions of the Federal Reserve. Their primary focus is on closely watching the Federal Reserve's next move, particularly regarding potential rate hikes, and analyzing the subsequent impact on market stability and overall financial markets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0702c16a40074abed0254fa2987a4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a4a995063bc2bf1c53d9019501ce065&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a40dc31e02c5c0febdae8449f769db0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8a835d63382015bc0073fd6f79ae0ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc8300849246981a965ff70c583daf4d</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;shchelochkov2019.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780046013</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ISAR-SHOCK Trial">
  <data key="d0">ISAR-SHOCK Trial</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The ISAR-SHOCK trial is a prospective, 2-center, randomized clinical trial comparing the Impella LP2.5 to IABP in patients with cardiogenic shock caused by acute myocardial infarction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Abiomed Europe GmbH">
  <data key="d0">Abiomed Europe GmbH</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Abiomed Europe GmbH is the manufacturer of the Impella LP2.5 device and provided support for the ISAR-SHOCK trial.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI)">
  <data key="d0">Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Acute myocardial infarction is a medical condition characterized by a sudden blockage of blood flow to the heart muscle, causing cardiogenic shock in the study patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI) is a medical condition</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiogenic Shock (CS)">
  <data key="d0">Cardiogenic Shock (CS)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cardiogenic shock is a condition of inadequate blood flow due to heart dysfunction, which the Impella LP2.5 and IABP are used to treat.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hemodynamic Support">
  <data key="d0">Hemodynamic Support</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hemodynamic support refers to the use of devices like Impella LP2.5 and IABP to improve blood flow</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1855c52c9abac15b97446b5b78a35eb2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiac Index (CI)">
  <data key="d0">Cardiac Index (CI)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cardiac Index (CI) is a hemodynamic parameter defined as the primary end point of the study, measuring change from baseline after device implantation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mean Arterial Pressure (MAP)">
  <data key="d0">Mean Arterial Pressure (MAP)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Mean Arterial Pressure (MAP) is a hemodynamic parameter used to calculate Cardiac Power Index (CPI), with changes observed in both Impella and IABP groups.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiac Power Index (CPI)">
  <data key="d0">Cardiac Power Index (CPI)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cardiac Power Index (CPI) is a calculated hemodynamic parameter derived from CI and MAP, used to assess cardiac function.&lt;SEP&gt;Cardiac Power Index is a hemodynamic parameter measured over time after device implantation in the clinical trial.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a62a3411d190c14c03fad25d62150ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump">
  <data key="d0">Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump (IABP) is a medical device used as a control treatment in a clinical trial, compared against Impella.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33f31a24de4f3032f5ab5311fd13365</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score">
  <data key="d0">Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score (MODS) is a scoring system used to assess organ dysfunction severity, measured at baseline and 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33f31a24de4f3032f5ab5311fd13365</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sepsis-Related Organ Failure Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Sepsis-Related Organ Failure Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sepsis-Related Organ Failure Assessment (SOFA) is a scoring system used to assess organ failure, measured at baseline and 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33f31a24de4f3032f5ab5311fd13365</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mortality">
  <data key="d0">Mortality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mortality refers to death as an outcome, assessed via 30-day survival curves in the clinical trial.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33f31a24de4f3032f5ab5311fd13365</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hemolysis">
  <data key="d0">Hemolysis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hemolysis is the breakdown of red blood cells, assessed by free hemoglobin levels, which were significantly higher in Impella patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Hemolysis is a potential adverse event or complication associated with Impella use.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33f31a24de4f3032f5ab5311fd13365&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c61ba2f73cda3eb90b84f74f9851e60</data>
  <data key="d4">seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045976</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
