<node id="Propionic Acidemia (PA)">
  <data key="d0">Propionic Acidemia (PA)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Propionic Acidemia (PA) is a medical condition studied in the referenced research, involving chronic kidney disease (CKD) manifestations.&lt;SEP&gt;Propionic Acidemia is a metabolic disorder characterized by minimal hepatic capacity to metabolize propionic acid, requiring renal excretion to clear toxic metabolites.&lt;SEP&gt;Propionic Acidemia is a metabolic disorder studied in the context of chronic kidney disease, affecting whole-body creatine synthesis and renal function.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61463c7b12c07a431ba8cba59dce8f00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3829da11ddccd396403f1961385f8e5</data>
  <data key="d4">shchelochkov2019.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD)">
  <data key="d0">Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) is a medical condition observed in PA patients, as described in the research.&lt;SEP&gt;Chronic Kidney Disease is a condition involving progressive loss of kidney function, with surveillance parameters including cystatin C, plasma uric acid, and 24-hour protein excretion.&lt;SEP&gt;Chronic Kidney Disease is a long-term complication observed in PA patients, defined by eGFR &lt;60 mL/min/1.73 m2.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61463c7b12c07a431ba8cba59dce8f00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3829da11ddccd396403f1961385f8e5</data>
  <data key="d4">shchelochkov2019.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cystatin C">
  <data key="d0">Cystatin C</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cystatin C is a biomarker used to estimate glomerular filtration rate (eGFR) and assess kidney function, measured in the study.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04</data>
  <data key="d4">shchelochkov2019.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Creatinine">
  <data key="d0">Creatinine</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Creatinine is a serum biomarker used to estimate GFR, but its levels in PA patients are influenced by diet, sarcopenia, and impaired synthesis.&lt;SEP&gt;Creatinine is a biomarker for kidney function, but its levels can be affected by factors in organic acidemias and renal tubular secretion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-518d22241c7304c17fbdf836ee4ebc04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61463c7b12c07a431ba8cba59dce8f00</data>
  <data key="d4">shchelochkov2019.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1780045994</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
